This paper is about neural language modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of regularization techniques in the proposed multilingual LM, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of LSTM layers in the model also suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance on low-resource data, which is a common concern in statistical learning (cs.SD).
